<title>SINGAPORE: IDT Holdings net profit jumps 43 pct.</title>
<headline>IDT Holdings net profit jumps 43 pct.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-06-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>January 10, 1996 (date of</p>
<p>incorporation) to March 31, 1997</p>
<p>		   (in millions of S$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net profit			    11.80  vs   8.24</p>
<p>    Dividend (cents)		     3.00  vs   n/a</p>
<p>    Group share (cents)		 14.90  vs  10.70</p>
<p>    Turnover				96.34  vs  75.74</p>
<p>    Other income incl. interest	0.48  vs   0.46</p>
<p>    Interest (expense)		   1.23  vs   1.37</p>
<p>    Depreciation (expense)	     2.20  vs   1.36</p>
<p>    Pre-tax profit			13.16  vs   9.39</p>
<p>    Tax					1.28  vs   1.07</p>
<p>    Minorities		   (loss)  0.08  vs   0.07 (loss)</p>
<p>Dividend pay date: To be announced</p>
<p>Last day books open: August 18, 1997</p>
<p>Note - IDT Holdings (Singapore) Ltd was incorporated on January 10, 1996 and debuted on the Stock Exchange of Singapore on January 27, 1997. The company specialises in liquid crystal display consumer electronic products.</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703011)</p>
